<font color="#FF0000">THE BUFFET ZONE!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 15 14:39:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Okay!  So..Big Deal!  Art goes to visit the troops in Witchita.  I was secretly impressed with his pair of dobermans, monocle, swagger stick, mother of pearl inletted clip board...boy did he ever have those wing wipers trembling in their safety shoes.<br>
After lunch, I went by to accoust him for screwing me and Toon Sarge on the tip (James and I both kicked in a quarter..but Pizza Bender only gave a nickle)..anyway he had already left...I knew without asking 'cause the dart board was back up on the wall, the checker boards were being set up and some guy was rolling in a barrel of beer.  You know how it is when the I.G. leaves the company area.  I screamed out that I was Art's idol and flashed my P-38.  You should have seen them scramble for their tool boxes...was going to inform the Meatball Muncher but didn't want to bust his bubble...Art likes to think of himself as a &quot;Hardass!&quot;<br>
Tried to call the Chinese waitress to apologize for bringing TS and DZ to her restuarant..but I kept getting a Wong number!  I'm just grateful that Mom didn't have to witness it...she would have &quot;miked&quot; them both..probably 40 mike mike High Explosive!  Can't figure out Green Grunt Gary wanting mom to &quot;mike&quot; him..but then again, all grunts have a crazy streak!  Maybe it's his way of being humble in front of Mom?<br>
I went back to the Peking Palace to give the girl another extra dime.  She began crying and asked if I would like another &quot;Cookie?&quot;  I slashed her throat with my P-38 and took her scalp.  Geez..it's strange how some words trigger a guy.<br><br>
MTF - Man to Favor
<p><code>-- By the way, Dented Zippo...  (they want their green napkin back) </code><p>


